Bootstrapping Mason

1. log in (as root) to computer running SUSE Linux
2. zypper se -s mason, see that 'perl-HTML-Mason' package is installed
3. also see that you have 'apache2' installed, minimally configured (e.g. 'chkconfig apache2 on' or
   systemd equivalent) and running
4. in /etc/sysconfig/apache2, see that APACHE_MODULES contains 'perl'
5. set up DNS, /etc/hosts or whatever for your Mason virtual host
5. in /etc/apache2/vhosts.d, create a configuration file for the virtual host with the following
contents:

<VirtualHost [my_virtual_hostname]:80>
    ServerAdmin ncutler@localhost
    ServerName [my_virtual_hostname]
    DocumentRoot /srv/www/mason/components
    HostnameLookups Off
    UseCanonicalName Off
    ServerSignature On
    # # # ENABLE MASON
    PerlOptions +Parent
    PerlSwitches -I/srv/www/mason/components/[my_lib_dir]
    PerlModule HTML::Mason::ApacheHandler
    <Directory "/srv/www/mason/components">
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride None
        Order allow,deny
        Allow from all
        SetHandler perl-script
        PerlHandler HTML::Mason::ApacheHandler
    </Directory>
</VirtualHost>

6. mkdir -p /srv/www/mason/components
7. chown -R wwwrun.www /srv/www/mason
8. create a test file /srv/www/mason/components/test.html

<html>
This is a test.
This <% "nothing but a <friggin> test" | h %>.
</html>

8. rcapache2 restart
9. point browser to http://[my_virtual_hostname]/test.html while praying to the Mason gods
10. test file should display correctly; if there are problems, see /var/log/apache2/error_log
11. unpack the mfile-mason distribution to [dist]
12. cp [dist]/etc/mfile-mason.conf /etc
13. edit /etc/mfile-mason.conf to taste (it controls this instance of mfile-mason)
14. ln -si [dist] /srv/www/mason/components
15. zypper in mariadb mariadb-client
16. set mysql root password
16. edit /etc/my.cnf and put mysql root password under [client]
17. dbinit/dbinit.sh (you may have to enter system root password)
18. assuming [dist] ends in "/mfile-mason", point browser at http://my_virtual_hostname/mfile-mason/start.html
